    "recap_headline": "Fresno State Athletics",
    "recap_text": "ST. GEORGE, Utah \u2013\nFresno State fell in a high-scoring\u00a0slugfest\u00a0on the road, dropping a 17\u201313 decision to Utah Tech on Tuesday night at Bruce Hurst Field.\nThe Bulldogs (7-13) pounded out 12 hits and scored in five different innings, but a pair of big innings from the Trailblazers proved too much to overcome as Utah Tech (14-8) collected 16 hits in the win.\nHow It Happened\nFresno State jumped on the board immediately as\nOwen Faust\nled off the game with a home run to left field. After Utah Tech answered with a solo shot in the bottom half, the Bulldogs put together a strong second inning, scoring three runs highlighted by\nMarcus Nolen's\nRBI double and a run-scoring\u00a0groundout\u00a0from Faust to take a 4\u20131 lead.\nThe momentum quickly shifted in the bottom of the second when Utah Tech erupted for five runs, capped by a three-run homer from Kyle McDaniel. The Trailblazers followed with a six-run third inning to build a 12\u20134 advantage.\nFresno State responded in the fourth, plating five runs to cut the deficit to 12\u20139.\nEthan Payne\ndelivered a two-RBI single, and\nCam Schneider\nadded a two-run hit later in the frame to bring the Bulldogs back within striking distance.\nSchneider continued his big night in the sixth inning, launching a three-run home run to pull Fresno State within one at 13\u201312. The Bulldogs eventually tied the game in the eighth on a sacrifice fly by Faust.\nHowever, Utah Tech answered decisively in the bottom of the eighth, scoring four runs, three of them unearned, to reclaim control at 17\u201313. Fresno State was unable to respond in the ninth.\nNotes\nCam Schneider\nled the Bulldogs with a home run and five\u00a0RBIs, finishing 2-for-4 with two runs scored.\nOwen Faust\nhomered to open the game and drove in three runs.\nEthan Payne\nwent 3-for-4 with two\u00a0RBIs\u00a0and a run scored.\nMarcus Nolen\nscored three times and added an RBI.\nSky Collins\nrecorded two hits and scored once.\nTyler Patrick\nallowed nine runs over 2.0 innings in the start.\nDrew Townson\nprovided length out of the bullpen, tossing 5.0 innings with five strikeouts.\nBJ Rodriguez\nwas tagged with the loss after allowing four runs (one earned) in the eighth inning.\nFresno State hit two home runs and totaled 10 walks in the game.\nThe Bulldogs scored 13 runs on 12 hits but committed two errors.\nUtah Tech scored 11 runs across the second and third innings combined.\nThe game lasted 3 hours and 32 minutes in 94-degree conditions.\nUp Next\nThe Bulldogs will play their final game against Utah Tech tomorrow, Friday, March 20, at 5:05 p.m. PT."
